ENTRY       EC 2.4.1.183                Enzyme
NAME        alpha-1,3-glucan synthase;
            uridine diphosphoglucose-1,3-alpha-glucan glucosyltransferase;
            1,3-alpha-D-glucan synthase;
            UDP-glucose:alpha-D-(1-3)-glucan 3-alpha-D-glucosyltransferase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Glycosyltransferases;
            Hexosyltransferases
SYSNAME     UDP-glucose:alpha-D-(1->3)-glucan 3-alpha-D-glucosyltransferase
REACTION    UDP-glucose + [alpha-D-glucosyl-(1->3)]n = UDP + [alpha-D-glucosyl-(1->3)]n+1 [RN:R03996 R06045]
ALL_REAC    R03996 R06045(G)
SUBSTRATE   UDP-glucose [CPD:C00029];
            [alpha-D-glucosyl-(1,3)]n [CPD:C02616]
PRODUCT     UDP [CPD:C00015];
            [alpha-D-glucosyl-(1,3)]n+1 [CPD:C02616]
COMMENT     A glucan primer is needed to begin the reaction, which brings about elongation of the glucan chains.
